Fix AOT compatibility in 4 LRO files in `/tmp/sv-5b13ff0e4fea41a3bc02c3bbb0e14bc3/before/`. Each file has a `ToObjectFromJson<Dictionary<string, string>>()` call that triggers IL2026/IL3050 because it uses reflection-based JsonSerializer internally.

In each of the 4 files below, replace the line:
```csharp
var lroDetails = ModelReaderWriter.Write(rehydrationToken, ModelReaderWriterOptions.Json, AzureResourceManagerContext.Default).ToObjectFromJson<Dictionary<string, string>>();
```

with:
```csharp
var lroData = ModelReaderWriter.Write(rehydrationToken, ModelReaderWriterOptions.Json, AzureResourceManagerContext.Default);
Dictionary<string, string> lroDetails;
using (var lroDoc = JsonDocument.Parse(lroData))
{
    lroDetails = new Dictionary<string, string>();
    foreach (var prop in lroDoc.RootElement.EnumerateObject())
    {
        lroDetails[prop.Name] = prop.Value.GetString();
    }
}
```

Also add `using System.Text.Json;` to the using directives if it's not already present, and add `using System.Collections.Generic;` if not already present.

The 4 files:
1. `ManagementGroup/Generated/LongRunningOperation/ManagementGroupsArmOperation.cs` (line 61)
2. `ManagementGroup/Generated/LongRunningOperation/ManagementGroupsArmOperationOfT.cs` (line 61)
3. `Resources/Generated/LongRunningOperation/ResourcesArmOperation.cs` (line 61)
4. `Resources/Generated/LongRunningOperation/ResourcesArmOperationOfT.cs` (line 61)

Fix AOT compatibility in serialization files in `/tmp/sv-5b13ff0e4fea41a3bc02c3bbb0e14bc3/before/`. Replace `JsonSerializer.Serialize(writer, ...)` calls with AOT-safe alternatives. 

These types all implement `IJsonModel<T>` with `WriteObjectValue` extension method support. Replace `JsonSerializer.Serialize(writer, obj)` with `writer.WriteObjectValue(obj, options)`. The `options` variable (`ModelReaderWriterOptions`) is always available in these methods.

For `ResponseError` (from Azure.Core), use `writer.WriteObjectValue(Error, options)` — the `WriteObjectValue` extension handles IJsonModel<T> types.

